reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 4, 2022
reviews.reviewText: i was super excited to try out this blush ! i am a sucker for cream/liquid blush so i was hoping this would be worth it. and it definitely was !! the formula is actually really really blendable and it’s pretty pigmented and you’re able to build it up as much as you desire. i bought the shade “Dolce Vita” and it’s perfect for my skin tone and i feel like would be able to use on deeper complexions. I am a makeup artist so this has been a staple for brides in my kit and it has worked beautifully on every single person i’ve used it on. The applicator looks like a nail polish brush which is different but nothing too crazy that one can’t figure out. it helps with getting the product right where you want it so it works just fine ! I’ve used it on days where i’m full glam and on days where i am not wearing foundation and it works just the same on either makeup look. it doesn’t cling on to foundation , which is a pet peeve of mine when it comes to cream blushes at times, and it blends smoothly when i apply powder blush on top 🫶🏼 If you’re contemplating getting this blush just do it i promise you won’t regret it ! ❤️❤️

reviews.reviewText: This blush is such a a pretty, pigmented color! The color is very very pigmented, so a little will go a long way.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 20, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars GET IT RIGHT NOW!
reviews.reviewText: I was looking for a nice easy liquid blush to try. I have never tried liquid blush before and to say this is so good! It is. Every blush or eyeshadow I tried using would always be a little patchy and I would have to use so much product! This blush (I have the 01 Pink in Love) is so good! It matches great and I can tell it would match just about every other skin tone. It’s super easy to apply, (try a little at a time) one little touch is enough for a side of your face. Not a glob or a brush, just a tiny speck. It is so pigmented and it stays on so well. I LOVE this blush and will order this from now on. I used a sponge, my finger, and a blush brush and all worked so much for application. Thank you Kimuse!Side comment: Don’t mind the sparkles on my face as it’s not normal. I tried out a liquid bronzer and as you can tell. It was just glittery vs bronzer.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 26, 2022
reviews.reviewText: I am 76 and probably have tried just about everything. I find this to be easy to use and looks like a natural finish. I had dental work done and for some reason thought I would use it as a lipstick. I applied it gently, and did not have any lip movement until it dried. At eight o'clock at night, I STILL had color on my lips, not a lot but I did not feel like I needed to apply lipstick! My new go-to long lipstick. You may feel a dryness, but it did not chap. Good Luck!

reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. The blush applicator is just a brush, exactly like nail polish brushes. The intensity is not that strong, in the sense that you may have to use more than a few dots. The product does not have a strong odor. Overall 4 out of 5 stars.
This blush is soo pigmented and looks so good on brown skin, i love it

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on April 11, 2023
reviews.reviewText: This is about the best blusher I’ve ever had. The colour I have (glistening rose) is beautiful. It goes on so so well and lasts all day. You only need a tiny tiny amount too. I put a little dot on each cheek and that little bit spreads everywhere! You don’t need anywhere as much as the picture above shows you. (And I like to wear make up so you can see it). I love it.

Great value. Goes on well. Isn't too pink. Bought because I'm older and wanted to see if this was better than powder. It didn't cake. Looked nice. Delivery was a day later than advertised but was still quick. I'd order again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on August 2, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Love this product. Can I ask where dolce vita has gone though? What colour would replace that one as it was perfect for me. Please bring it back, other than that! All time favourite blush.

I really love this blush. this is one of the nicest blushes I own. It’s extremely pigmented, easy to blend out and is exactly the color i was looking for. I would 100% but this blush again. The only thing I wish was different would be the packaging, due to the cap not being able to twist on properly but that doesn’t really make a difference to the product itself.
